  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_8' aria-label=\" Dhanasingh Prabhu versus Chandrasekar & Another pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('8','2025','2025_7_655_692','2025INSC831'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DHANASINGH PRABHU<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>CHANDRASEKAR & ANOTHER </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 655</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 831</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007782025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : B.V. NAGARATHNA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, SATISH CHANDRA SHARMA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court was right in dismissing the complaint on the ground that the name of the partnership firm was not mentioned in the statutory notice issued by the appellant/complainant to the respondents u/s.138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 and was also not in the complaint filed by the appellant/complainant. Headnotes&dagger; Negotiable Instrument Act, 1881 &ndash; ss.138, 141 &ndash; Partnership Act, 1932 &ndash; Appellant-complainant advanced a loan of Rs.21,00,000/- to the respondent nos.1 and 2 (a partneship firm) for business purposes<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 14-07-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2994/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Case Allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('8','2025','2025_7_655_692','2025INSC831','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'